When an error occurs while a page is being rendered for rss, the logging context is not too useful:
{noformat}
 -- url: /createrssfeed.action | userName: someguy | action: createrssfeed
{noformat}

Most of the time the error is due to a particular page, but unless somebody has actually been to that page and generated the error there, it's not too helpful.  Ideally, the logging context should include the title of the item being rendered too.

Replicated using the following wiki markup. See screenshot for results:

{code:none}
|| One || Two || Three || Four ||
| onetwothreefourfivesixseveneightninetenonetwothreefourfivesixseveneightnineten | two | three | onetwothreefourfivesixseveneightninetenonetwothreefourfivesixseveneightnineten |
{code}

Rich text editor doesn't escape the following string properly.
{code}
(*) (**)
{code}

If you type it and then start switching between Rich Edit and Wiki Markup tabs escaping will change as well.

