It would be nice if Confluence has a way to ignore a malfunctioning LDAP server. This will be helpful in situation where multiple repositories are defined in atlassian-user.xml and one of the repository is down. Currently, although the other repositories are still accessible, it is very slow since Confluence always connects to the malfunctioning LDAP server until it times out. Situation will be even worse if LDAP servers are located in different countries altogether.

