In Space Admin, simply granting 'Restrict Pages' privileges does not allow a user to restrict pages. 'Create Pages' is required as well as 'Restrict Pages'.

To reproduce:

# Turn off serving JavaScript in header via _Confluence Admin > General Configuration > Feature Settings > JavaScript served in header_
# Go to any space and select the Documentation Theme
# Reload the page

The sidebar will load incorrectly at the top of the page, and the following JavaScript error will be reported:

{code:none}
AJS is not defined
http://localhost:8080/s/2032/1/1.6/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.doctheme:resources/doc-theme.js
Line 205
{code}

{panel:title=Workaround|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Turn on serving JavaScript in header via _Confluence Admin > General Configuration > Feature Settings > JavaScript served in header_
{panel}

Marking this as major because the error message is misleading and causing unnecessary pain for support.

In {{FileSystemAttachmentDataDao.getDeleteErrorReason()}} there are two bugs, see inline comments below:
{code}
    private static String getDeleteErrorReason(File attachmentFolderForThisPage)
    {
        if(!attachmentFolderForThisPage.exists())
        {
            return REASON_DIR_DOES_NOT_EXIST;
        }

        if(!attachmentFolderForThisPage.isDirectory())
        {
            return REASON_NOT_A_DIRECTORY;
        }

        if(attachmentFolderForThisPage.listFiles().length > 2)   // as pointed out by Don, this should be 0
        {
            return REASON_NOT_EMPTY;
        }

        if(attachmentFolderForThisPage.canWrite()) // this should be a case where the directory is not writeable
        {
            return REASON_NOT_WRITABLE;
        }

        return REASON_UNKNOWN;
    }
{code}

