A customer ([CSP-53878|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/CSP-53878] - not accessible to public) has reported that when using IE 7/8/9 to access Confluence through an iFrame, it will display the login page. After keying in the login details and hit login, it will still redirect the user back to login page. This seems to be that cookies are not accepted by it whereby IE treat Confluence as third party.

Steps to reproduce:
# Create a html page with the following code:
#* {code:html}
<iframe src="http://extranet.atlassian.com" width="100%" height="600" />
{code}
# Try to access the page in browser and try to log in using IE 7/8/9

\\
It would be nice if it is possible to add a P3P header in any Confluence page that set cookies.

Useful reference (pointed by customer): [http://adamyoung.net/IE-Blocking-iFrame-Cookies]

